('wk1_06', 'ccc_06', 'ccc_02', 1, '2017-09-08', '18:30:00', 'Scalise Field, Sage Park, Berlin', 1, 0, 14, 6, 7, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, 'ccc_02', 'Berlin Uses Ground Attack to Beat Bulkeley', 'James Mazzarella, Zach Hrubiec, and Alex Halkias all recorded rushing touchdowns to help Berlin beat the co-op of Bulkeley, HMTCA, and Weaver 27-0 in a CCC inter-division game Friday at Sage Park in Berlin. \r\n\r\nMazzarella opened the scoring with a 1-yard TD run, finishing with 7 rushes for 52 yards, and was the game''s leading receiver with 4 catches for 101 yards. Hrubiec was the leading rusher with 12 carries for 73 yards, including a 7-yard run to put Berlin (1-0) ahead 14-0 before halftime.\r\n\r\nHalkias scored on a 2-yard run in the third quarter, and kicker Giancarlo Tufano recovered a fumble and returned it 25 yards for the game''s final points in the fourth. Berlin quarterback Kevin Dunn was 10-for-21 with 182 yards and an interception. For Bulkeley (0-1), QB Luis Diaz was 8-for-16 for 112 yards and an interception.', 'Second Quarter\r\nB-James Mazzarella 1 run (Giancarlo Tufano kick)\r\nB-Zach Hrubiec 7 run (Tufano kick)\r\nThird Quarter\r\nB-Alex Halkias 2 run (kick failed)\r\nFourth Quarter\r\nB-Tufano 25 fumble return (Tufano kick)', 'BH', 'B', 0, 27, NULL),
