('wk1_22', 'ccc_16', 'ccc_32', 1, '2017-09-08', '19:00:00', 'Jack OBrien Stadium, Windsor High School', 1, 0, 7, 14, 7, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, 'ccc_32', 'Jackson, Defense Lead Windsor To Victory', 'Quarterback Julian Jackson threw two touchdown passes to support a stout team defensive effort, helping Windsor defeat Maloney 28-0 in a CCC interdivision game Friday at O''Brien Field in Windsor.\r\n\r\nJackson connected with L.J. Wollcott and Jerry Woodard on TD passes of 34 and 25 yards respectively in the third quarter. Woodard also recorded an interception. Windsor''s (1-0) defense had five sacks and held Maloney (0-1) to 60 yards of total offense.\r\n\r\nShuan Hunter scored the game''s first points on a 1-yard TD run in the second quarter, and Camoz Johnson scored on a 4-yard run in the fourth.', 'Second Quarter\r\nW-Shuan Hunter 1 run (Jerry Woodard kick)\r\nThird Quarter\r\nW-L.J. Wollcot 34 pass from Julian Jackson (Woodard kick)\r\nW-Woodard 25 pass from Jackson (Woodard kick)\r\nFourth Quarter\r\nW-Camoz Johnson 4 run (Woodard kick)', 'M', 'W', 0, 28, NULL),
