('wk1_53', 'ccc_26', 'ccc_21', 1, '2017-09-09', '12:00:00', 'Northwest Catholic High School', 1, 0, 0, 6, 0, NULL, 14, 8, 7, 6, NULL, 'ccc_26', 'Catania, Ferreira Set Pace for Rocky Hill', 'Joe Catania and Joe Ferreira combined for 239 rushing yards to help Rocky Hill topple Northwest Catholic 35-6 in a CCC Div. III West game Saturday at Northwest Catholic High School.\r\n\r\nFerreira had 11 rushes for 128 yards, and scored when he recovered a ball fumbled by Catania and returned it 65 yards to the end zone. Catania had 20 carries for 111 yards. Anthony Feliciano had a second fumble recovery for Rocky Hill (1-0), scoring on a 6-yard return. Will White and Danny Cavallaro had TD runs of 3 and 4 yards respectively, and Rocky Hill also scored on a safety when a Northwest Catholic (0-1) punt was snapped out of the end zone. \r\n\r\nSpencer Merkel had a 50-yard TD run for Northwest Catholic, scoring the team''s only points.', 'First Quarter\r\nRH-Joe Ferreira 65 fumble recovery (Catania kick)\r\nRH-Will White 3 run (Catania kick)\r\nSecond Quarter\r\nRH-Anthony Feliciano 6 fumble recovery (kick failed)\r\nRH-Safety (punt snap out of end zone)\r\nThird Quarter\r\nNW-Spencer Merkel 50 run (run failed)\r\nRH-Danny Cavallaro 4 run (Catania kick)\r\nFourth Quarter\r\nRH-Matt Osgood 15 pass from Cavallaro (kick failed)\r\n', 'RH', 'NWC', 35, 6, NULL),
