('wk2_14', 'ccc_15', 'ccc_16', 2, '2017-09-15', '18:30:00', 'Falcon Field, Meriden', 1, 15, 13, 21, 0, NULL, 8, 0, 0, 6, NULL, 'ccc_16', 'Graham Leads Maloney to First Win', 'Quarterback Larue Graham accounted for four touchdowns, as Maloney scored 49 unanswered points en route to a 49-14 victory over Hartford Public in a CCC interdivision game Friday at Falcon Field in Meriden.\r\n\r\nGraham put his team ahead with a 40-yard TD pass to Chris Infante and connected with Preston Studley and Aden Valentin on scoring passes of 5 and 11 yards respectively. Graham also had a 9-yard rushing TD and was 13-for-23 through the air for 231 yards. Valentin and Studley also had TD runs of 12 and 2 yards respectively in the second half, and James Tarver ran for a 7-yard score for Maloney (1-1). Infante had 6 catches for 137 yards.\r\n\r\nLavarey Banton scored the game''s first points for Hartford Public (0-2) on a 5-yard TD run, and also reached the end zone on a 17-yard run in the fourth. He finished with 30 carries for 167 yards.', 'First Quarter\r\nHP--Lavarey Banton 5 run (Jermaine Jones pass from Joemar Scott)\r\nM--Larue Graham 9 run (Preston Studley pass from Graham)\r\nM--Chris Infante 40 pass from Graham (Adam Williams kick)\r\nSecond Quarter\r\nM--Studley 5 pass from Graham (Williams kick)\r\nM--Aden Valentin 11 pass from Graham (kick failed)\r\nThird Quarter\r\nM--Valentin 12 run (Williams kick)\r\nM--Studley 2 run (Williams kick)\r\nM--James Tarver 7 run (Williams kick)\r\nFourth Quarter\r\nHP--Banton 17 run (pass failed)', 'HP', 'M', 14, 49, NULL),
