('wk2_51', 'pqt_18', 'pqt_08', 2, '2017-09-15', '19:00:00', 'Granby Memorial High School', 1, 15, 14, 0, 14, NULL, 0, 6, 0, 0, NULL, 'pqt_08', NULL, NULL, 'First Quarter\r\nG--Jackson Rome 6 run (Sam Attianese pass from Logan Disabella)\r\nG--Disabella 2 run (Matt Zyzdorf kick)\r\nSecond Quarter\r\nG--Keon Lawrence 32 run (Zyzdorf kick)\r\nG--Christian Warren 51 pass from Rome (Zyzdorf kick)\r\nWL--Miguel Gonzalez 46 pass from Jameson Gill (run failed)\r\nFourth Quarter\r\nG--Warren 11 run (Zyzdorf kick)\r\nG--Disabella 20 pass from Rome (Zyzdorf kick)', 'WL', 'G', 6, 43, NULL),
('wk2_52', 'ccc_13', 'ccc_28', 2, '2017-09-16', '11:00:00', 'South Windsor High School', 1, 7, 0, 0, 7, NULL, 0, 3, 0, 6, NULL, 'ccc_28', NULL, 'South Windsor defeated Glastonbury 14-9 after Connor Kapisak punched in their second touchdown from the goal line late in the fourth. A 63-yard touchdown catch by Colin Ryan in the first quarter would ultimately separated the two teams. \r\n\r\nSouth Windsor focused on running the ball throughout the game with 24 carries for 94 yards, but their offense came down to two huge passes between Kapisak and Ryan. The two 63-yard receptions by Ryan made up 126 of Kapisak''s 134 passing yards.\r\n\r\nAlthough Glastonbury answered with their own rushing touchdown from quarterback Drew Daniels on the 1-yard line, it was not enough to overcome South Windsor. They had a chance to tie up the game in the second quarter, but the drive failed and they were forced to kick a field goal. \r\n\r\nDrew Daniels would end the game completing 6 of 14 passes with 82 yards in addition to 30 rushing yards and one touchdown on 14 carries. ', 'First Quarter\r\nSW--Colin Ryan 63 pass from Connor Kapisak (Cameron Plourde kick)\r\nSecond Quarter\r\nG--Ryan Smith 27 field goal\r\nFourth Quarter\r\nSW--Kapisak 1 run (Plourde kick)\r\nG--Drew Daniels 1 run (pass failed)', 'G', 'SW', 9, 14, NULL),
