('wk2_55', 'ecc_10', 'ecc_01', 2, '2017-09-16', '12:00:00', 'Bacon Academy', 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'ecc_10', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 20, 14, NULL),
('wk2_56', 'pqt_12', 'pqt_14', 2, '2017-09-16', '12:00:00', 'Old Saybrook High School', 1, 6, 15, 7, 7, NULL, 0, 0, 6, 6, NULL, 'pqt_14', NULL, 'Victor Pascoe and Vincent Dyer made up the entire Old Saybrook/Westbrook football''s offense as it defeated Nonnewaug 35-12, scoring all five touchdowns between them. \r\nThe chemistry between the two quickly showed with Dyer catching a touchdown from Pascoe to open up scoring. Pascoe would show he was just as lethal by himself on the ground, scoring 45- and 37-yard rushing touchdowns. Dyer was on the end of two touchdown receptions in the first half and put the final nail in the coffin with a 40-yard touchdown run at the end of the game. \r\nNonnewaug''s offense didn''t get started until the third quarter when Jarrett Michaels ran in a touchdown for 10 yards. By the time he scored a second rushing touchdown from the three yards out in the fourth the game was already out of hand. ', 'First Quarter\r\nOSW--Vincent Dyer 15 pass from Victor Pascoe (kick blocked)\r\nSecond Quarter\r\nOSW--Pascoe 45 run (Dyer run)\r\nOSW--Dyer 18 pass from Pascoe (Cooper Pavlovich kick)\r\nThird Quarter\r\nOSW--Pascoe 37 run (Pavlolich kick)\r\nN--Jarrett Michaels 10 run (kick missed)\r\nFourth Quarter\r\nN--Michaels 3 run (pass failed)\r\nOSW--Dyer 40 run (Pavlovich kick)', 'N', 'OSW', 12, 35, NULL),
('wk2_57', 'ccc_30', 'ccc_01', 2, '2017-09-16', '13:00:00', 'Avon High School', 1, 6, 0, 0, 0, NULL, 7, 7, 7, 13, NULL, 'ccc_30', NULL, 'Sophomore quarterback Ryan Carlson shined on both offense and defense as Tolland defeated Avon 34-6.\r\n\r\nCarlson took control of the game on the ground, rushing for 164 yards and four touchdowns on 18 carries, as well as in the air, throwing for 73 yards. 63 of those yards went to Jonny Lindquist, who also contributed two field goals and four extra points.  \r\n\r\nCarlson also added 15 tackles on defense to help hold Avon to only six points. He was aided by Collin Cook who forced an Avon fumble on the first play from scrimmage and ended the game with 9 tackles. \r\n\r\n', 'First Quarter\r\nT--Ryan Carlson 2 run (Jonny Lindquist kick)\r\nA--Brady Gordon 1 run (kick blocked)\r\nSecond Quarter\r\nT--Carlson 25 run (Lindquist kick)\r\nThird Quarter\r\nT--Carlson 7 run (Lindquist kick)\r\nFourth Quarter\r\nT--Lindquist 32 field goal\r\nT--Carlson 2 run (Lindquist kick)\r\nT--Lindquist 26 field goal\r\n', 'T', 'A', 34, 6, NULL),
('wk2_58', 'ccc_21', 'ccc_24', 2, '2017-09-16', '13:00:00', 'RHAM High School', 1, 0, 21, 0, 9, NULL, 6, 0, 0, 14, NULL, 'ccc_24', NULL, 'Dylan Depersia scored two touchdowns one a forced fumble recovery to help RHAM high school defeat Northwest Catholic 30-20 in CCC inter conference play at RHAM high school.\r\n\r\nDepersia returned an interception for 30 yards for a touchdown as well as having 12 sacks. Dan Grenier had a 25 yard interception return with Kevin Clark scoring a safety in the final quarter.\r\n\r\nNorthwest Catholic''s Spencer Merkel ran 19 and 25 yards with Nicholas Good catching a 38 yard pass from Connor Rich in the fourth.', 'First quarter\r\nN--Spencer Merkel 19 run (kick fail)\r\nSecond quarter\r\nR—Cal Redman 1 run (Dan Grenier kick)\r\nR—Dylan Depersia 30 fumble recovery (Grenier kick)\r\nR—Grenier 25 interception return (Grenier kick)\r\nFourth quarter\r\nN--Merkel 25 run (Merkel conversion)\r\nR—Depersia 30 interception return (Grenier kick)\r\nR—Kevin Clark (Safety)\r\nN—Nicholas Good 38 pass from Connor Rich (Conversion fail)', 'N', 'R', 20, 30, NULL),
('wk2_59', 'pqt_19', 'pqt_07', 2, '2017-09-16', '13:00:00', 'Gilbert High School', 1, 7, 14, 7, 0, NULL, 0, 6, 2, 8, NULL, 'pqt_07', NULL, 'Gilbert/Northwestern defeated Rockville 28-16 after showcasing a powerful running game. Billy Komons scored three rushing touchdowns of 5, 7, and 14 yards to make up the majority of his team''s points. \r\nIn addition to Komons, Brad Lissy would open the game with a 2-yard rushing touchdown to take the lead for Gilbert/Northwestern. Rockville would never catch back up, despite quarterback Ben Ambro completing 24 of 45 passes for 290 yards and two touchdowns. \r\nAmbro was assisted by Nick Foley and Jay Van Oudenhove, two receivers that caught touchdown passes for 13- and 11-yards, respectively. On defense, Jonathan St. Germain was able to force a safety in the third quarter. ', 'First Quarter\r\nG--Brad Lissy 2 run (Chris Nanni kick)\r\nSecond Quarter\r\nG--Billy Komons 7 run (Nanni kick)\r\nR--Nick Foley 13 pass from Ben Ambro (kick failed)\r\nG--Komons 5 run (Nanni kick)\r\nThird Quarter \r\nG--Komons 14 run (Nanni kick)\r\nR--Safety by Jonathan St. Germain\r\nFourth Quarter\r\nR--Jay Van Oudenhove 11 pass from Ambro (Tyler Allen pass from Ambro)\r\n', 'R', 'G', 16, 28, NULL),
