('wk2_65', 'pqt_16', 'pqt_01', 2, '2017-09-16', '13:00:00', 'Canton High School', 1, 0, 14, 0, 12, NULL, 21, 14, 13, 7, NULL, 'pqt_16', NULL, 'Colton Engel delivered a 58-26 victory for Stafford/East Windsor/Somers over Canton, dominating both sides of the field and snatching a tough win after the team suffered through a stomach bug this week. \r\n\r\nEngel was the engine to SSEW''s offense; he carried the ball for 165 yards and two touchdowns on eight carries and completed 6 of 9 passes for 108 yards and a touchdown. He was also the rock in the middle of the defense, registering two tackles, a fumble recovery, and a touchdown return on one of two interceptions.\r\n\r\nBesides Engel, Jeff Kology disrupted the Canton offense with five tackles, three for a loss, and Luke Phillips completed 7 of 8 extra point attempts. \r\n\r\nAfter the game, coach Brian Mazzone said, "We had battles all week with the stomach bug and 18 different kids missed practice. I was really proud of the way the kids stepped up, it was a hot, miserable day and we played tough."\r\n', 'First Quarter\r\nS--Colton Engel 4 run (Luke Phillips kick)\r\nS--Engel 27 interception return (Phillips kick)\r\nS--Cody Gebo 16 pass from Tyler Ouellette (Phillips kick)\r\nSecond Quarter\r\nS--Engel 70 run (Phillips kick)\r\nS--Julien Revis 43 pass from Engel (Phillips kick)\r\nC-#2 79 pass from #12 (run failed)\r\nC--#40 10 pass from #12 (#12 run)\r\nThird Quarter\r\nS--Revis 10 run (Phillips kick)\r\nS--Revis 11 run (kick failed)\r\nFourth Quarter\r\nC--#2 79 pass from #12 (run failed)\r\nS--Evan Gardener 4 run (Phillips kick)\r\nC--#6 70 run (pass failed)', 'SEW', 'C', 58, 26, NULL),
('wk2_66', 'alt_04', 'ind_03', 2, '2017-09-16', '13:00:00', 'Dillon Stadium, Hartford', 1, 26, 6, 7, 6, NULL, 0, 0, 8, 0, NULL, 'ind_03', NULL, 'Kyle Zajack had five passing touchdowns and rushed for a sixth to give Capital Prep a 45-8 win against New Mission (Hyde Park, MA) at Dillon Stadium in an out of conference game.\r\n\r\nZajack was 10 for 12 with 308 yards passing to put Capital Prep ahead. John Edwards had six touches for 152 yards and two touchdowns throughout the game with O''Neil Robinson and Mike Slade also receiving passes form Zajack.\r\n\r\nAndrew Finklin scored New Mission''s touchdown with Takari Hobbs running for the two point conversion.', 'First quarter\r\nCA—John Edwards 56 pass from Kyle Zajack (kick failed)\r\nCA—O’Neil Robinson 13 pass from Zajack (Tyler Oney kick)\r\nCA—Mike Slade 40 pass from Zajack (Oney kick)\r\nCA—Edwards 25 pass from Zajack (kick failed)\r\nSecond quarter\r\nCA—Robinson 62 pass from Zajack (kick failed)\r\nThird Quarter\r\nNM—Andrew Finklin 4 run  (Takari Hobbs run)\r\nCA—Zajack 1 run (Renaldo Downer kick)\r\nFourth quarter\r\nCA—Slade 10 pass from Solomon Barlow (kick fail)\r\n', 'NM', 'CA', 8, 45, NULL),
('wk2_67', 'pqt_15', 'pqt_10', 2, '2017-09-16', '13:00:00', 'Lewis Mills High School', 1, 6, 6, 0, 0, NULL, 7, 7, 0, 6, NULL, 'pqt_15', NULL, 'Despite eight turnovers on offense, SMSA/University/Classical football defeated Lewis Mills 20-12, not allowing a single point in the second half. Their record improves to 1-1 while Lewis Mills drops to 0-2. \r\n\r\nJordan Rivera and Devon Daniels led the tight defense that only allowed 85 yards rushing and 81 yards in the air, combining for 25 tackles with 4 for a loss. Rivera added a forced fumble and recovery, while Daniels contributed a sack. \r\n\r\nOffensively Devin Hill struggled with his judgement, throwing five interceptions in comparison to his two touchdowns. The biggest weapon the Tigers had in their victory was Josh McLeggon, who sealed the game with a 16-yard rushing touchdown in the fourth quarter and also pulled in five receptions for 112 yards and a touchdown. \r\n', 'First Quarter\r\nSU--Naseim Harrison 57 pass from Devin Hill (Hayden Jordan kick)\r\nLM--Chris Romano 7 run (kick failed)\r\nSecond Quarter\r\nLM--Romano 5 run Romano (run failed)\r\nSU--Josh McLeggon 59 pass from Hill (Jordan kick)\r\nFourth Quarter\r\nSU--McLeggon 16 run (kick failed)', 'SU', 'LM', 20, 12, NULL),
('wk2_68', 'ccc_02', 'ccc_09', 2, '2017-09-16', '13:30:00', 'Cheney Tech High School', 1, 0, 8, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 24, 7, 14, NULL, 'ccc_02', NULL, 'Kevin Dunn led Berlin to a 45-8 victory over East Catholic, completing 6 of 9 passes for 161 yards and two touchdowns. Scoreless after the first quarter, Berlin scored 24 points in the second to take a dominant 24-8 lead going into the half. \r\n\r\nThe versatility of Larry St. Pierre and Alex Halkias were crucial to the victory, with each player scoring both rushing and receiving touchdowns. Halkias rushed for 87 yards on nine carries and St. Pierre gained 87 yards on three catches, including a 58 yard touchdown reception. \r\n', 'First Quarter\r\nSecond Quarter\r\nB--Alex Halkias 58 pass from Kevin Dunn (Giancarlo Tufano kick)\r\nEC-- Touchdown\r\nB--Tufano 27 field goal\r\nB--Larry St. Pierre Jr. 7 run (Tufano kick)\r\nB--St. Pierre 58 pass from Dunn (Tufano kick)\r\nThird Quarter\r\nB--James Mazzarella 5 run (Tufano kick)\r\nFourth Quarter\r\nB--Halkias 45 run (Marco Scarano kick)\r\nB--Shane Gallagher 43 run (Scarano kick)', 'B', 'EC', 45, 8, NULL),
