('wk3_06', 'ccc_32', 'ccc_11', 3, '2017-09-22', '18:30:00', 'Farmington High School', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 13, 14, 14, NULL, 'ccc_32', 'Hunter, Johnson Score Twice Each For Windsor', 'Shaun Hunter and Tomasz Johnson had two rushing touchdowns each, leading Windsor to a 41-0 road win over Farmington in a CCC Div. II East game Friday at Farmington High.\r\n\r\nHunter scored on runs of 2 and 6 yards, respectively, while Johnson scored on runs of 15 and 8 yards. Quarterback Julian Jackson opened the scoring for Windsor (3-0) with a 22-yard touchdown pass to Jerry Woodard toward the end of the first half and later connected with Ljay Walcott on a 57-yard scoring strike. Windsor’s defense forced five turnovers within a 17-minute period on the game clock, during which all of the game’s points were scored. With the loss, Farmington fell to 0-3.\r\n', 'Second Quarter\r\nW-Jerry Woodard 22 pass from Julian Jackson (Jerry Woodard kick)\r\nW-Tomasz Johnson 15 run (kick failed)\r\nThird Quarter\r\nW-Ljay Walcott 57 pass from Jackson (Woodard kick)\r\nW-Shaun Hunter 2 run (Woodard kick)\r\nFourth Quarter\r\nW-Hunter 6 run (Woodard kick)\r\nW-Johnson 8 run (Woodard kick)', 'W', 'F', 41, 0, NULL),
('wk3_07', 'ccc_05', 'ccc_16', 3, '2017-09-22', '18:30:00', 'Falcon Field, Meriden', 1, 0, 14, 14, 6, NULL, 0, 0, 7, 0, NULL, 'ccc_16', NULL, 'Larue Graham scored three touchdowns in the air and one on the ground to help lift Maloney over Bristol Eastern in a CCC Div. II West game at Falcon Field, Meriden. \r\n\r\nGraham completed 13-of-23 passes for 204 yards and three touchdowns, in addition to a 1-yard rushing touchdown in the third quarter. He was in tune with receiver Victor Marquez, who caught eight catches for 125 yards and two touchdowns, as well as a two-point conversion for Maloney (3-0). Bristol Eastern falls to 0-3 on the year. \r\n', 'Second Quarter\r\nM-Aden Valentin 6 run (Adam Williams kick)\r\nM-Victor Marquez 13 pass from Larue Graham (Williams kick)\r\nThird Quarter\r\nBE-Ariza Kolloverja 7 run (John McPhee kick)\r\nM-Graham 1 run (kick failed)\r\nM-Marquez 20 pass from Graham (Marquez pass from Graham)\r\nFourth Quarter\r\nM-Chris Infante 28 pass from Graham (kick failed)', 'BE', 'M', 7, 34, NULL),
('wk3_08', 'ccc_21', 'ccc_02', 3, '2017-09-22', '18:30:00', 'Scalise Field, Sage Park, Berlin', 1, 0, 7, 7, 10, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, 'ccc_02', NULL, 'Alex Halkias ran for two touchdowns and caught a 47 yard pass for another to help Berlin win 24-0 at home against Northwest Catholic in a CCC interdivision game from Scalise Field at Sage Park in Berlin.\r\n\r\nHalkias had 12 carries for 125 yards and caught a pass from Kevin Dunn for his first touchdown of the game. Halkias followed that with a third quarter touchdown of 40 yards and another TD run of 17 yards in the fourth. Dunn was 9-for-12 for 130 yards and Giancarlo Tufano had five catches for 51 yards. Tufano also kicked a 37 yard field goal to cap off the scoring for Berlin (3-0).\r\n\r\nParis Carpenter had 11 carries for 68 yards for Northwest Catholic (0-3) and Kai Fleming had two catches for 29 yards.\r\n', 'Second Quarter\r\nB-Alex Halkias 47 pass from Kevin Dunn (Giancarlo Tufano kick)\r\nThird Quarter\r\nB-Halkias 40 run (Tufano kick)\r\nFourth Quarter\r\nB-Halkias 17 run (Tufano kick)\r\nB-Tufano 37 field goal\r\n\r\n', 'NWC', 'B', 0, 24, NULL),
