('wk3_23', 'ccc_17', 'ccc_29', 3, '2017-09-22', '19:00:00', 'Southington High School', 1, 7, 14, 9, 7, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, 'ccc_29', NULL, 'Tim O''Shea caught two touchdown passes from Will Barmore to help lead Southington to a CCC interdivsion victory over Manchester from home at Southington High. \r\n\r\nO''Shea had six receptions for 81 yards, including TD catches of 14 and 21 yards. Barmore was 20-for-30 passing for 187 yards and three touchdowns, connecting with Jamie Lamson from 13-yards out in the first quarter to open the scoring for Southington (3-0). Tanner LaRosa added 17 carries for 85 yards, including a 2 yard TD run in the second quarter. Eli Ford led the Manchester (0-3) rushing attack with 25 yards on eight carries.\r\n', 'First Quarter\r\nS-Jamie Lamson 13 pass from Will Barmore (Conversion kick Evan Johanns)\r\nSecond Quarter\r\nS-Tim O’Shea 14 pass from Barmore (Johanns kick)\r\nS-Tanner LaRosa 2 run (Johanns kick)\r\nThird Quarter\r\nS-O’Shea 21 pass from Barmore (Johanns kick)\r\nS-Safety (ball was sent out of in-zone)\r\nFourth Quarter\r\nS-Ian Agnew 20 run (Johanns kick)\r\n', 'M', 'S', 0, 37, NULL),
('wk3_24', 'ccc_15', 'ccc_18', 3, '2017-09-22', '19:00:00', 'Middletown High School', 1, 14, 17, 7, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 16, NULL, 'ccc_18', NULL, 'Xzavier Reyes ran for three touchdowns to help Middletown beat Hartford Public 38-16 in a CCC Div. II East game Friday night at home at Middletown High.\r\n\r\nReyes had 21 carries for 190 yards on the night, scoring twice in the first quarter on runs of 1 and 3 yards. He added a 35-yard touchdown run in the second quarter that gave Middletown a 21-0 lead. Stone Belzo passed for 107 yards in addition to the 281 yards Middletown (3-0) gained on the ground. Mike Aresco was successful in kicking a 21-yard field goal late in the second half and also completed all five extra point attempts.\r\n\r\nHartford Public (0-3) scored all 16 of their points in the fourth quarter. Joemar Scott was 12-for-17 passing for 119 yards and one touchdown, a 9-yard pass from Zinodine Stewart for Public’s last score. Lavarey Banton added a 26-yard TD run, as well.\r\n', 'First Quarter\r\nM-Xzavier Reyes 1 run (Mike Aresco kick)\r\nM-Reyes 3 run (Aresco kick)\r\nSecond Quarter\r\nM-Reyes 35 run (Aresco kick)\r\nM-DeAaron Lawrence 7 pass from Stone Belzo (Aresco kick)\r\nM-Aresco 21 kick\r\nThird Quarter\r\nM-Tyreece Lumpkin 17 run (Aresco kick)\r\nFourth Quarter\r\nHP-Lavarey Banton 26 run (Jermain Jones pass from Joemar Scott)\r\nHP-Zinodine Stewart 9 pass from Scott (Jones pass from Scott)', 'HP', 'M', 16, 38, NULL),
